title: RESTART reboots the story (ADR-248 acceptance)
story: dungeo
author: Sharpee Team
description: In-game RESTART delegates through platform events; the harness
  reboots in place with a fresh story instance (fresh module state, fresh
  daemons). The ack renders as the final packet of the old engine, and the
  rebuilt world starts over — including state that was mutated before the
  restart.
---

# Mutate world state away from the initial configuration
> look
[OK: contains "West of House"]

> open mailbox
[OK: contains "leaflet"]

> take leaflet
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> north
[OK: contains "North of House"]

# Restart: the old engine acks, then the harness reboots
> restart
[OK: contains "The story restarts."]
[OK: not contains "I don't understand"]
[OK: not contains "Restart failed"]

# Fresh boot: opening location again
> look
[OK: contains "West of House"]

# State reset proof: the mailbox is closed again with the leaflet back inside
> open mailbox
[OK: contains "leaflet"]
